   large language models) for the purpose of producing software
   substantially similar in interface, behavior, or function to the
   Software.

4. COMMERCIAL USE AND ROYALTY

   This section applies to your use of the Software in any Product if
   any of the following is true:

   (a) the Product generates revenue, directly or indirectly;
   (b) the Product is developed, owned, or operated by an organization
       that has accepted external equity, debt, or grant funding from
       venture capital firms, angel investors, family offices, or
       other institutional investors (excluding founder contributions,
       customer revenue, pre-orders, and individual crowdfunding under
       USD $250 per backer); or
   (c) the Product is used internally by a for-profit organization to
       support a revenue-generating activity.

   "Product" means any software you distribute, sell, license, make
   available as a service to third parties, or operate internally for
   commercial purposes.

   Royalty: a royalty applies to commercial use of the Software once
   a Product exceeds a revenue threshold. The specific revenue
   threshold and royalty rate are being calibrated and will be
   finalized by the copyright holder before forbear v1.0. Royalty
   terms will be communicated to commercial users at the time of
   notification (see below) and will not exceed customary industry
   practice for application UI frameworks.

   Funded organizations under (b) whose Product has not yet generated
   qualifying revenue accept the terms of this section but owe no
   royalty until qualifying revenue begins.

   Notification: if your Product crosses USD $100,000 in gross revenue
   during any trailing 12-month period, you must contact the copyright
   holder at gabriel.readme@hey.com within 30 days. No payment is due 
   at this stage — this notification establishes communication before the
   royalty threshold is reached, allows the copyright holder to provide
   any applicable support, and confirms acceptance of the license terms
   in writing.

   This section does not apply, and the Software remains free, when:

   (i) the Product is distributed under an OSI-approved open-source
       license;
   (ii) the user is a natural person, or a group of natural persons,
        using the Product for personal or non-commercial purposes, AND
        no organization meeting criterion (b) has any ownership or
        operational interest in the Product; or
   (iii) the user is a non-profit organization using the Product in
         furtherance of its non-profit mission.

   Royalties are self-reported and paid quarterly to the copyright
   holder. Contact gabriel.readme@hey.com to arrange payment.

5. LIMITED MAINTENANCE COMMITMENT

   For users whose Product has earned qualifying revenue under §4 and
   whose royalty payments are current, the copyright holder commits to:

   (a) shipping bug fixes in regular releases of the Software; and
   (b) issuing security patches for the major version the user has
       adopted, for 18 months after that version's release.

   No other warranty, support obligation, response-time guarantee, or
   service-level commitment is granted, express or implied. This
   commitment lapses if royalty payments are more than 60 days overdue.

